The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, December 27, 2002 				 Freebies for mobile users
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Dec. 26: On the eve of the launch of Reliance Infocomms limited mobility service, cellular operators took pre-emptive steps to retain their customers by doling out freebies. The two mobile cellular operators in Delhi  Bhartis AirTel and Batatas Idea  are offering an additional free airtime worth Rs 50 and Rs 100 respectively, to prepaid subscribers who renew their account by December 27. 																								A senior executive in Hutch, AirTels leading competitor in Delhi said, We want our subscribers to get a feel of the new service and compare it with the one available to them. We are yet to announce any such scheme.																								While refusing to accept that the company has initiated the scheme to retain its customers, an AirTel spokesperson said, AirTel had recently run a contest on theme Bollywood. The winners walked away with VCDs, T-shirt and caps. As a consolation prize, we have announced free airtime worth Rs 50 for a select few customers if they recharge before December 27. This is to help the company load the free airtime on the subscribers card by the end of the month. 
